concepts.term: for any horizontal wave, for all X-ray projections along oblique directions-that is, any orientation that is not vertical-we can say one thing: if you do the vertical line integral, the wave has a positive cycle and a negative cycle that cancel out

evidence: For waves at one-degree orientation, you need projections at ninety degrees plus one degree-the orthogonal direction.
triples.s: projection at ninety degrees plus one degree
